<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════
     SECTION 2: WHY THIS AREA
════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2ead4); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#b98229; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:400; font-variation-settings:'opsz' 32; line-height:1.2; color:#191817; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">A compact northern suburb with practical amenity and consistent buyer demand.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Taigum is a small, well-positioned suburb approximately 12 kilometres north of the Brisbane CBD, bordered by Zillmere to the west, Boondall to the east and Bracken Ridge to the north. Its compact boundaries are one of its strengths: residents are genuinely close to everything they need, from the Taigum Square Shopping Centre to the broader retail hub at Westfield Chermside, which is within a 10-minute drive. The housing stock runs from post-war weatherboard and brick through to early contemporary builds, with a mix of owner-occupiers and investors who have held properties in the suburb for many years.
    </p>
<!-- APPRAISAL FORM -->
