<!-- END APPRAISAL FORM -->
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Taigum sits at an interesting point in the northern corridor buyer decision. It offers a lower entry price than Aspley, Bracken Ridge or Boondall while delivering comparable northside convenience and lifestyle. Buyers who need to be practical about budget but are not prepared to compromise on access to amenity consistently identify Taigum as a suburb that delivers on both counts. Investors also look here, attracted by the rental demand generated by workers in the northern corridor and the hospitals in the area.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      I know the northern corridor well and understand how buyers make suburb comparisons when they are working within a realistic budget. Taigum is a suburb that rewards honest positioning and correct pricing against recent sales. When a campaign here is run properly, it attracts real competition from buyers who have been watching the market and know this suburb offers value.
    </p>
