    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:400; font-variation-settings:'opsz' 32; line-height:1.2; color:#191817; margin-bottom:2.5rem;">Common questions about Taigum.</h2>
    <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column;">

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What drives property values in Taigum?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Taigum property values are driven by block size, street character and proximity to the Taigum Square Shopping Centre. Buyers comparing the suburb against Zillmere and Boondall find it offers a quieter residential feel at a comparable price point, which attracts family buyers and investors seeking northside rental returns. Properties on the suburb's internal streets, away from main road exposure, consistently outperform in campaigns.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          How long does it take to sell a home in Taigum?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Well-priced Taigum homes typically sell within 30 to 50 days. The suburb draws buyers from the broader northern corridor who are attracted by practical amenity, proximity to Westfield Chermside and a price point that sits below Aspley. Investors also participate actively, drawn by rental demand from the northern suburbs workforce. Correct pricing and honest presentation of the property produce the fastest, strongest results here.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What is the lifestyle like in Taigum?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Taigum is a compact, practical suburb approximately 12 kilometres north of the CBD. The Taigum Square Shopping Centre provides everyday retail, and Westfield Chermside is within a 10-minute drive. Bus services connect the suburb to the wider northern corridor. The housing stock is predominantly post-war and early contemporary homes on decent-sized blocks, and the suburb has a stable owner-occupier residential character.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          Is Taigum a good suburb to buy in right now?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Taigum offers genuine value for buyers who need practical northside access and everyday convenience without paying the premium of Aspley or Chermside. Its compact geography means amenity is genuinely close, and the suburb attracts both families looking for an affordable entry and investors who see rental demand holding firm in the northern corridor.</p>
      </details>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

